ssionContinuityService(db_session).refresh_for_session(\nbackend/tests/test_continuity_service.py:290:        source_summary=\"Accepted beat sheet.\",\nbackend/tests/test_continuity_service.py:296:    assert row.source_summary == \"Accepted beat sheet.\"\nbackend/tests/test_continuity_service.py:298:    facts = ContinuityBibleData.model_validate(row.summary_data).facts\nbackend/tests/test_continuity_service.py:302:        ContinuityFactCategory.CHARACTER,\nbackend/tests/test_continuity_service.py:303:        ContinuityFactCategory.LOCATION,\nbackend/tests/test_continuity_service.py:304:        ContinuityFactCategory.OBJECT,\nbackend/tests/test_continuity_service.py:305:        ContinuityFactCategory.PROMISE,\nbackend/tests/test_continuity_service.py:306:        ContinuityFactCategory.VOICE_CONSTRAINT,\nbackend/tests/test_continuity_service.py:307:        ContinuityFactCategory.UNRESOLVED_THREAD,\nbackend/tests/test_continuity_service.py:308:        ContinuityFactCategory.LOCKED_DETAIL,\nbackend/tests/test_continuity_service.py:316:    session_id = _seed_continuity_session(db_session)\nbackend/tests/test_continuity_service.py:317:    service = SessionContinuityService(db_session)\nbackend/tests/test_continuity_service.py:322:        source_summary=\"Accepted beat sheet.\",\nbackend/tests/test_continuity_service.py:326:        source_stage=WorkflowStage.COMPOSITION,\nbackend/tests/test_continuity_service.py:327:        source_summary=\"Prepared composition context.\",\nbackend/tests/test_continuity_service.py:334:    assert second.source_summary == \"Accepted beat sheet.\"\nbackend/tests/test_continuity_service.py:340:    session_id = _seed_continuity_session(db_session)\nbackend/tests/test_continuity_service.py:341:    service = SessionContinuityService(db_session)\nbackend/tests/test_continuity_service.py:345:        source_summary=\"Accepted beat sheet.\",\nbackend/tests/test_continuity_service.py:359:        source_summary=\"Resynced continuity after downstream invalidation.\",\nbackend/tests/test_continuity_service.py:366:    facts = ContinuityBibleData.model_validate(refreshed.summary_data).facts\nbackend/tests/test_continuity_service.py:369:    assert any(fact.category == ContinuityFactCategory.LOCKED_DETAIL for fact in facts)\ndocs/frontend-design-foundation.md:13:- Color: bedtime-friendly ink, surface, brand, moss, gold, and rose tones are\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:21:        |         +--> AI adapters for planning, composition, and narration\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:25:        +--> background workers for composition and audio generation\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:42:## Why Composition and Audio Must Use Resumable Server-Side Jobs\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:44:Composition and narration are long-running operations that cannot safely live inside request threads or browser memory. They need server-side jobs because:\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:63:- `ai/`: Gemini planning, composition, and narration adapters\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:77:- Pitch batch and selected pitch\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:78:- Character batch and selected character sheet\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:79:- Beat sheet\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:82:- Continuity bible\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:83:- Composition job and segments\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:103:Story setup preferences such as word count, runtime, and chapter count are planning hints rather than hard limits. The system should use them to guide prompts, estimates, and editing suggestions without forcing exact compliance at the expense of story quality or bedtime tone.\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:168:          Start a fresh bedtime story to open the workspace and begin the first\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:312:        title=\"Pick up where bedtime left off.\"\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.tsx:380:          description=\"In-progress and completed stories are grouped separately so it is clear whether you should resume work or revisit a finished bedtime story.\"\nbackend/tests/test_chat_action_contracts.py:181:                            \"job_kind\": \"composition\",\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.test.tsx:145:        'Start a fresh bedtime story to open the workspace and begin the first session.',\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:163:        \"CompositionChunkEventPayload\": {\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:172:              \"$ref\": \"#/$defs/CompositionChunkKind\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:258:          \"title\": \"CompositionChunkEventPayload\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:261:        \"CompositionChunkKind\": {\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:267:          \"title\": \"CompositionChunkKind\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:270:        \"CompositionChunkRealtimeEvent\": {\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:315:              \"$ref\": \"#/$defs/CompositionChunkEventPayload\"\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:340:              \"const\": \"composition\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:341:              \"default\": \"composition\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:346:              \"const\": \"composition.chunk\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:347:              \"default\": \"composition.chunk\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:360:          \"title\": \"CompositionChunkRealtimeEvent\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:552:            \"composition\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1330:            \"composition\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1514:          \"composition.chunk\": \"#/$defs/CompositionChunkRealtimeEvent\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1534:          \"$ref\": \"#/$defs/CompositionChunkRealtimeEvent\"\nbackend/tests/test_session_beat_sheet_service.py:52:                bedtime_softening_note=(\nbackend/tests/test_session_beat_sheet_service.py:53:                    f\"{label} stays bedtime-safe by keeping tension readable and quickly soothed.\"\nbackend/tests/test_session_beat_sheet_service.py:80:                bedtime_notes=\"Keep every pressure beat quickly buffered by warmth and visibility.\",\nbackend/tests/test_session_beat_sheet_service.py:103:    snapshot = service.create_session(working_title=\"Beat Sheet Stage\")\nbackend/tests/test_session_beat_sheet_service.py:116:            bedtime_safety_concerns=[\"Keep every surprise quickly reassuring.\"],\nbackend/tests/test_session_beat_sheet_service.py:146:        bedtime_goal=\"feel sleepy and safe by the ending\",\nbackend/tests/test_session_beat_sheet_service.py:188:def test_refine_beat_sheet_creates_selected_revision_and_invalidates_composition(\nbackend/tests/test_session_beat_sheet_service.py:209:        stage=WorkflowStage.COMPOSITION,\nbackend/tests/test_session_beat_sheet_service.py:219:        bedtime_goal=\"settle into a visibly sleepy ending\",\nbackend/tests/test_session_beat_sheet_service.py:253:        stage=WorkflowStage.COMPOSITION,\nbackend/tests/test_session_beat_sheet_service.py:264:                \"bedtime_goal\": \"Let the harbor settle into an even sleepier ending.\",\nbackend/tests/test_session_beat_sheet_service.py:307:    assert \"Story setup and composition need refresh.\" in (\ndocs/frontend-state-architecture.md:60:  label: 'Accepted revised beat sheet',\ndocs/system-diagram.md:10:    Worker[\"Worker process<br/>composition jobs, audio jobs, retries, interruption\"]\ndocs/system-diagram.md:13:    Gemini[\"Gemini adapters<br/>planning, composition, narration\"]\ndocs/system-diagram.md:28:    Worker -->|\"planning, composition, TTS calls\"| Gemini\ndocs/system-diagram.md:42:Word count, runtime, and chapter count are soft planning hints. They shape prompts and estimates, but the system should favor story quality, bedtime tone, and coherent pacing over exact numeric compliance.\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:29:| `selection.recorded` | Accepted or candidate selection for genre, tone, pitch, character sheet, beat sheet, or story setup. | `user` | stage-specific |\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:31:| `content.user_edit.recorded` | Structured user-authored edits to durable planning or composition records. | `user` | stage-specific |\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:34:| `composition.progress.recorded` | Durable composition job progress for replay and worker debugging. | `system` | `composition` |\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:57:  \"invalidated_stages\": [\"pitches\", \"characters\", \"beats\", \"composition\", \"audio\", \"finalize\"],\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:75:  \"summary_text\": \"Updated beat sheet notes from the workspace.\"\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:96:- `record_composition_progress(...)`\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:128:event_log.record_composition_progress(\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:130:    job_id=composition_job.id,\nfrontend/src/api/catalog.ts:10:  bedtime_safety_notes?: string | null\nfrontend/src/api/catalog.ts:21:  bedtime_notes?: string | null\ndocs/product-brief.md:5:Storyteller is a session-based bedtime story creation studio. It helps a user move from a loose story idea to a finished written story and finished narration audio, with the ability to leave and come back later without losing progress.\ndocs/product-brief.md:11:- Bedtime-first: stories should support calm endings, emotional repair, and low-friction read-aloud use.\ndocs/product-brief.md:25:5. Character sheet generation, again with selection and refinement.\ndocs/product-brief.md:26:6. Save-the-Cat beat sheet generation and editing.\ndocs/product-brief.md:28:8. Composition in segments with visible progress, typewriter-like output, and interruptibility.\ndocs/product-brief.md:52:### Composition Experience\ndocs/product-brief.md:80:- create and revise a bedtime story plan\nbackend/tests/test_character_generation_service.py:38:                            \"The cast supports the selected pitch by turning the bedtime quest \"\nbackend/tests/test_character_generation_service.py:41:                        bedtime_safety_notes=(\nbackend/tests/test_character_generation_service.py:52:                            bedtime_safety_notes=(\nbackend/tests/test_character_generation_service.py:72:                                bedtime_safety_notes=(\nbackend/tests/test_character_generation_service.py:93:                        bedtime_safety_notes=(\nbackend/tests/test_character_generation_service.py:94:                            \"The mystery stays bedtime-safe because each reveal is named, \"\nbackend/tests/test_character_generation_service.py:104:                            bedtime_safety_notes=(\nbackend/tests/test_character_generation_service.py:124:                                bedtime_safety_notes=(\nbackend/tests/test_character_generation_service.py:166:            summary=\"A calm cast for the harbor bedtime story.\",\nbackend/tests/test_character_generation_service.py:167:            story_function=\"The cast supports the pitch with a gentle bedtime lane.\",\nbackend/tests/test_character_generation_service.py:168:            bedtime_safety_notes=(\nbackend/tests/test_character_generation_service.py:169:                \"Everything stays safe because it is calm and bedtime-friendly.\"\nbackend/tests/test_character_generation_service.py:178:                bedtime_safety_notes=\"Mira stays safe because helpers stay nearby always.\",\nbackend/tests/test_character_generation_service.py:189:                    bedtime_safety_notes=\"Otis keeps each obstacle gentle and readable.\",\nbackend/tests/test_character_generation_service.py:218:            \"bring each light home before bedtime.\"\nbackend/tests/test_character_generation_service.py:237:        \"bedtime_safety_notes_are_grounded\": True,\nfrontend/src/api/sessions.ts:71:  bedtime_safety_concerns: string[]\nfrontend/src/api/sessions.ts:85:  bedtime_notes?: string | null\nfrontend/src/api/sessions.ts:116:  bedtime_softening_note?: string | null\nfrontend/src/api/sessions.ts:136:  bedtime_notes?: string | null\nfrontend/src/api/sessions.ts:142:  bedtime_goal?: string | null\nfrontend/src/api/sessions.ts:157:  bedtime_safety_notes?: string | null\nfrontend/src/api/sessions.ts:173:  bedtime_notes?: string | null\nfrontend/src/api/sessions.ts:174:  bedtime_safety_notes?: string | null\nfrontend/src/api/sessions.ts:221:export type ContinuityFactView = {\nfrontend/src/api/sessions.ts:237:export type ContinuityBibleView = {\nfrontend/src/api/sessions.ts:243:  facts: ContinuityFactView[]\nfrontend/src/api/sessions.ts:262:  bedtime_guardrail?: string | null\nfrontend/src/api/sessions.ts:293:  bedtime_goal?: string | null\nfrontend/src/api/sessions.ts:329:export type CompositionJobView = {\nfrontend/src/api/sessions.ts:496:  bedtime_softening_note?: string | null\nfrontend/src/api/sessions.ts:503:  bedtime_notes?: string | null\nfrontend/src/api/sessions.ts:504:  bedtime_goal?: string | null\nfrontend/src/api/sessions.ts:524:  latest_composition_job?: CompositionJobView | null\nfrontend/src/api/sessions.ts:526:  active_composition_job?: CompositionJobView | null\nfrontend/src/api/sessions.ts:530:  continuity_bible?: ContinuityBibleView | null\nfrontend/src/api/sessions.ts:595:  bedtime_goal?: string | null\nfrontend/src/api/sessions.ts:662:  bedtime_goal?: string | null\ndocs/domain-model.md:11:- Composition and audio are long-running workflows backed by durable records, not one-shot request responses.\ndocs/domain-model.md:32:| `active_composition_job_id` | Current composition job, if writing or rewrite work is running. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:41:such as pitches, character sheets, beat sheets, and setup revisions point back to the owning\ndocs/domain-model.md:49:| `story_session` | Root aggregate for one bedtime-story project. | IDs, title, stage pointers, overall status, timestamps. | Owns the current accepted choices and job pointers. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:51:| `genre` | Curated genre catalog entry. | slug, label, description, bedtime-safety notes, arc notes. | Backend-owned reference data. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:52:| `tone_profile` | Curated tone option linked to a genre. | `genre_id`, slug, label, descriptors, bedtime notes, default planning hints. | Tone choices are filtered by genre. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:54:| `pitch` | One candidate story premise. | batch or generation group, summary, hook, bedtime notes, selection flag. | `selected_pitch_id` on the session represents the accepted pitch; selection does not require a separate table. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:56:| `beat_sheet` | Structured Save-the-Cat plan. | ordered beats, bedtime-adaptation notes, revision. | Must be editable and versioned. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:58:| `composition_job` | Parent job record for writing or rewriting text. | status, progress, attempt count, stop reason, current segment pointer. | Not listed in the prompt title, but needed to make `composition_segment` durable and resumable. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:59:| `composition_segment` | One planned or written segment of the story. | segment index, planned summary, text, revision number, superseded segment, status. | Supports interruption, partial persistence, and rewrites of earlier sections. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:61:| `session_asset` | Durable artifact metadata for session files and exports. | asset kind, object path, MIME type, byte size, checksum, segment index, readiness status. | Covers draft snapshots, composition segments, audio segments, `.docx`, and final audio without scanning object storage. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:74:| 5 | `characters` | Characters | One character sheet is accepted. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:75:| 6 | `beats` | Beat sheet | One beat sheet is accepted. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:77:| 8 | `composition` | Composition | The current story text is complete enough to hand off to narration. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:95:| `in_progress` | Durable work is actively being produced or updated. | Pitch generation is running, composition is streaming segments, or audio rendering is underway. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:96:| `completed` | The stage has an accepted output that is still valid relative to all upstream dependencies. | A beat sheet was accepted and no upstream planning change has made it stale. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:97:| `needs_regeneration` | The stage was completed before, but an upstream change made its accepted output stale. The old output may remain visible for comparison, but it is not the current source of truth. | The user edits characters after a beat sheet exists, so beats, composition, audio, and finalize become stale. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:112:`genre -> tone -> brief -> pitches -> characters -> beats -> story_setup -> composition -> audio -> finalize`\ndocs/domain-model.md:131:| `genre` | `tone`, `brief`, `pitches`, `characters`, `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:132:| `tone` | `brief`, `pitches`, `characters`, `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:133:| `brief` | `pitches`, `characters`, `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:134:| `pitches` | `characters`, `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:135:| `characters` | `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:136:| `beats` | `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:137:| `story_setup` | `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:138:| `composition` | `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:145:- They still influence later composition, but a new pitch or character sheet does not automatically erase the user's preferred target length.\ndocs/domain-model.md:147:## Composition Interruption and Rewrite Rules\ndocs/domain-model.md:149:Composition is intentionally more flexible than the earlier planning stages.\ndocs/domain-model.md:151:- A composition job may move between `in_progress`, paused, resumed, or cancelled states without leaving the `composition` stage.\ndocs/domain-model.md:153:- A rewrite request against an earlier segment creates a new `composition_job` or new segment revision rather than mutating history in place.\ndocs/domain-model.md:155:- Any accepted composition rewrite marks `audio` and `finalize` as `needs_regeneration`.\ndocs/domain-model.md:156:- If the user decides the plan itself is wrong, they may navigate back to `beats` or `story_setup`, accept changes there, and let the backend mark `composition` and later stages stale.\ndocs/domain-model.md:166:   - Example: `composition`, `audio`, and `finalize` were `completed`, then the user edits the beat sheet.\ndocs/domain-model.md:167:   - Result: `composition`, `audio`, and `finalize` become `needs_regeneration`, and `resume_stage = composition`.\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_service.py:13:    CompositionJob,\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_service.py:14:    CompositionJobKind,\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_service.py:144:def test_policy_escalates_story_setup_edits_when_an_active_composition_job_would_be_invalidated(\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_service.py:151:        composition_status=JobStatus.IN_PROGRESS,\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_service.py:202:        and effect.stages == [WorkflowStage.COMPOSITION]\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_service.py:207:        and effect.job_kind == \"composition\"\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_service.py:319:        mark_composition_completed=True,\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_service.py:356:        mark_composition_completed=True,\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_service.py:427:    composition_status: JobStatus | None = None,\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_service.py:429:    mark_composition_completed: bool = False,\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_service.py:435:    snapshot = service.create_session(working_title=\"Bedtime Harbor\")\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_service.py:518:    composition_job = None\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_service.py:519:    if composition_status is not None:\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_service.py:522:            stage=WorkflowStage.COMPOSITION,\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_service.py:525:        composition_job = CompositionJob(\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_service.py:529:            job_kind=CompositionJobKind.DRAFT,\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_service.py:530:            status=composition_status,\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_service.py:534:        db_session.add(composition_job)\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_service.py:536:    elif mark_composition_completed:\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_service.py:539:            stage=WorkflowStage.COMPOSITION,\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_service.py:552:            source_composition_job_id=composition_job.id if composition_job else None,\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_service.py:565:                composition_job_id=composition_job.id if composition_job else None,\nbackend/tests/test_action_policy_service.py:578:        \"composition_job_id\": composition_job.id if composition_job else None,\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:8:Storyteller is a session-based bedtime story studio, not a single-shot prompt demo. A user needs to move through a staged workflow, leave, come back later, and still see the current plan, generated text, generated audio, and recent activity.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:14:- composition and audio generation are too slow and failure-prone to run inside request threads\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:24:All Gemini text, planning, composition, and narration calls belong behind backend-owned adapters and services.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:41:- brief, pitch batch, selected pitch\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:42:- character sheet candidates and selection\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:43:- beat sheet\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:45:- composition jobs and segment progress\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:56:- Story exports, intermediate composition files, narration segments, and final audio artifacts live in object storage.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:63:The browser needs live updates during composition and audio generation, and those updates need to remain tied to durable backend state.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:73:Composition and audio generation run in a worker process that is separate from the API process.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:85:- They guide pitch generation, beat planning, and composition prompts.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:87:- They should not be enforced as exact cutoffs that distort story quality or bedtime tone.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:89:The product should prefer a coherent, calm bedtime story over exact numeric compliance. If the system misses a target, it should do so transparently and gracefully rather than by truncating or padding the story unnaturally.\nbackend/tests/test_storage.py:123:        \"sessions/session-123/composition/jobs/compose-01/segments/0007.md\"\nbackend/tests/test_storage.py:135:        file_stem=\"bedtime-story\",\nbackend/tests/test_storage.py:138:        \"sessions/session-123/audio/jobs/audio-job-02/final/bedtime-story.mp3\"\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.md:40:| `composition` | `start_composition`, `pause_job`, `resume_job`, `redirect_composition`           | Job control is explicit and stage-bound. Redirects require concrete instructions.                     |\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.md:65:- All composition and audio job control actions\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.md:66:- `redirect_composition`\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.md:98:      \"action_type\": \"start_composition\",\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.md:99:      \"target_stage\": \"composition\",\nbackend/tests/test_brief_normalization_adapter.py:41:    assert \"bedtime_safety_concerns\" in prompt\nbackend/tests/test_brief_normalization_adapter.py:73:                                                \"A harbor bedtime quest where each lantern \"\nbackend/tests/test_brief_normalization_adapter.py:85:                                                \"bedtime_safety_concerns\": [\nfrontend/index.html:9:      content=\"Storyteller is a calm studio for crafting bedtime stories from first idea to finished narration.\"\ndocs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:21:beat-sheet generation, setup updates, composition rewrites, or audio start-up.\ndocs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:42:| `generate_beat_sheet` | `beats` | `background` | `story.generate_beat_sheet` | `refine_beat_sheet`, `regenerate_beat_sheet` | `StageOperationToolResult` | marks `beats` in progress and invalidates composition work |\ndocs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:43:| `update_setup_heuristics` | `story_setup` | `direct` | `story.update_setup_heuristics` | `update_story_setup` | `UpdateSetupHeuristicsToolResult` | creates a selected `story_setups` revision, records user-edit and selection events, invalidates downstream stages, cancels active composition/audio jobs |\ndocs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:44:| `compose_next_segment` | `composition` | `background` | `story.compose_next_segment` | `start_composition` | `CompositionToolResult` | cancels active composition jobs, creates a composition job, seeds a segment row, records initial progress |\ndocs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:45:| `rewrite_segments` | `composition` | `background` | `story.rewrite_segments` | `start_composition`, `redirect_composition` | `CompositionToolResult` | cancels active composition jobs, creates a rewrite job, seeds a revised segment row, records initial progress |\ndocs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:46:| `estimate_audio_length` | `audio` | `direct` | `story.estimate_audio_length` | `start_audio_generation` | `EstimateAudioLengthToolResult` | computes an estimate from composition segments or story-setup targets without mutating durable state |\ndocs/bedtime-guidelines.md:1:# Bedtime Safety and Content Guidelines\ndocs/bedtime-guidelines.md:3:Storyteller needs one shared definition of \"bedtime-safe\" so planning, writing, and narration do\ndocs/bedtime-guidelines.md:9:Bedtime-safe does not mean flat or boring. The product should still support:\ndocs/bedtime-guidelines.md:17:The constraint is emotional intensity, not imagination. A good bedtime story can move, surprise,\ndocs/bedtime-guidelines.md:61:- [`backend/app/models/bedtime_guidelines.py`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/models/bedtime_guidelines.py)\ndocs/bedtime-guidelines.md:62:- [`backend/app/ai/bedtime_guidelines.py`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/ai/bedtime_guidelines.py)\ndocs/bedtime-guidelines.md:66:- `backend/app/models/bedtime_guidelines.py` stores the preset key, active-vs-planned audience\ndocs/bedtime-guidelines.md:68:- `backend/app/ai/bedtime_guidelines.py` renders stage-specific prompt fragments for `pitch`,\ndocs/bedtime-guidelines.md:69:  `character`, `beat`, `composition`, and `audio`.\ndocs/bedtime-guidelines.md:77:That keeps the bedtime rules centralized instead of rewording them independently in each template.\ndocs/bedtime-guidelines.md:82:`shared_bedtime_default`, for a broad bedtime read-aloud audience. The backend also stores a plan\ndocs/bedtime-guidelines.md:98:The pipeline hook is already in place through `bedtime_guideline_preset_key` on the prompt context\ndocs/bedtime-guidelines.md:107:from app.ai.bedtime_guidelines import build_bedtime_guidelines_fragment\ndocs/bedtime-guidelines.md:109:fragment = build_bedtime_guidelines_fragment(\ndocs/bedtime-guidelines.md:110:    stage=\"composition\",\ndocs/bedtime-guidelines.md:111:    preset_key=\"shared_bedtime_default\",\ndocs/bedtime-guidelines.md:115:That call returns the shared bedtime policy plus stage-specific instructions for the requested\ndocs/bedtime-guidelines.md:116:pipeline step. Composition and audio fragments already exist even though those prompt templates are\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:1082:.plan-revision-panel__composition-note,\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:2096:.continuity-inspector__list {\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:2104:.continuity-inspector__list li {\nfrontend/src/styles/inde