{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_124","type":"agent_message","text":"Implemented and committed the prompt-assembly work in `71aa06e feat(prompt-57): composition prompt assembly`.\n\nThe backend now has a dedicated composition prompt schema and service, and both `compose_next_segment` and `rewrite_segments` use that shared assembler before seeding durable job/segment records. The assembled package separates stable system instructions from dynamic segment context and persists a debuggable prompt payload into composition job metadata and segment payloads.\n\nVerification:\n- `cd backend && python -m pytest tests/test_composition_prompt_assembly.py tests/test_story_tools.py -q` -> `21 passed`\n- `cd backend && python -m ruff format --check ...touched files...` -> passed\n- `cd backend && python -m ruff check ...touched files...` -> passed\n- `cd backend && python -m pytest -q` -> `205 passed, 5 skipped`\n\nI did not run browser checks because this task only changed backend prompt assembly and tests. The required reviewer summary was written to [`summary.md`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.yolopilot/runs/20260331T205548_storyteller_prompt_pack/57_composition_prompt_assembly/summary.md)."}}
